-- Ceragon Networks Heads for Biggest Two-Year Surge in Tel Aviv
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-07-19T08:03:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-19/ceragon-networks-heads-for-biggest-two-year-surge-in-tel-aviv.html
  Ceragon Networks Ltd. (CRNT)  headed for
the biggest advance in almost two years after the U.S. shares of
the maker of wireless networking systems jumped yesterday.  The  shares  gained 6.9 percent, the biggest rise since
August 2010, to 32.98 shekels, or the equivalent of $8.22, at
10:30 a.m. in  Tel Aviv . The U.S.-traded shares jumped 6.5
percent to $8.21 yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
